==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ross
<hw>Ross</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>; 115), <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>The rough, scaly matter on the surface of the
bark of trees.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ross</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ross
<hw>Ross</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To divest of the ross, or rough,
scaly surface; <as>as, to <ex>ross</ex> bark</as>.</def> <mark>[Local,
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rossel</ent>⟦br⟧
